      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOUNT JULIET NZ (5) made an immediate impact on debut last week, overcoming an early break to score by 7.7 metres at this circuit and distance. Starts from the 10m mark this time but should be better for the experience so can make it two for two. POZZI TONOZZI (1) was well in the betting at her first career run and was looming in the straight but locked wheels and broke before winding up third. Starts from the inside and could be hard to stop. FRAZZLED (4) was the horse that POZZI TONOZZI locked wheels with last week before he went on to finish runner-up. Has plenty of scope for improvement. HARPERS FERRY (2) led and faded to fourth on debut but could be better for the outing.",
